5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to manufactured homes; to amend Section
10 32-20-21, Code of Alabama 1975; to authorize Alabama
11 Department of Revenue to issue certificates of title to
12 current owners of manufactured homes model year 1999 and
13 earlier; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to
14 update the existing code language to current style.
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. Section 32-20-21, Code of Alabama 1975, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 "§32-20-21
20 No certificate of title shall be issued for any of the
21 following:
22 (1) A manufactured home owned by the United States or
23 any agency thereof.
24 (2) A manufactured home owned by a manufacturer or
25 licensed manufactured home dealer and held for sale.
26 (3) A manufactured home owned by a nonresident of this
27 state and not located in this state.
28 (4) Manufactured homes designated 1999 and prior year
Page 1

(4) Manufactured homes designated 1999 and prior year
HB435 Engrossed
29 models, unless requested by a current owner pursuant to this
30 article.
31 (5) Modular homes.
32 (6) A manufactured home situated in this state and
33 permanently affixed to the real property on which it is placed
34 and for which the certificate of title or the manufacturer's
35 certificate of origin has been cancelled canceled pursuant to
36 subsection (b) of Section 32-20-20(b).
37 (7) Any other manufactured homes as prescribed by the
38 department."
39 Section 2. This act shall become effective on January
40 1, 2027.
